-- Taiyo Oil to Resume Shikoku No.1 Crude Unit After Maintenance
-- B y   Y u j i   O k a d a
-- 2012-07-10T06:10:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-10/taiyo-oil-to-resume-shikoku-no-1-crude-unit-after-maintenance.html
Taiyo Oil Co., an unlisted Japanese
refiner, will resume the 88,000 barrel-a-day No. 1 crude
distillation unit at its Shikoku refinery in the country’s west
today after maintenance.  The company plans to idle the refinery’s 32,000 barrel-a-
day No. 2 crude unit from July 15 to Aug. 5, Yasushi Mukai, a
company spokesman, said by phone from  Tokyo .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuji Okada in Tokyo at 
